{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_01TmPXdaFPaS4gPKZ894Qsb5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No existing SLO constants. Here's the complete implementation:\n\n---\n\n## Implementation\n\n### New file: `config/monitoring/prometheus-rule.yaml`\n\nThe two relevant counters are:\n- `mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total` — failed inspections\n- `mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total` — total pods processed (which includes inspections)\n\nThe alert computes a failure rate over a 30-minute window and fires when it exceeds 5%.\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: monitoring.coreos.com/v1\nkind: PrometheusRule\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: prometheusrule\n    app.kubernetes.io/instance: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: monitoring\n    app.kubernetes.io/created-by: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/part-of: multiarch-tuning-operator\n    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: kustomize\n  name: controller-manager-alerts\n  namespace: system\nspec:\n  groups:\n    - name: multiarch-tuning-operator.rules\n      rules:\n        - alert: MultiarchImageInspectionFailureRateCritical\n          expr: |\n            (\n              rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total[30m])\n              /\n              rate(mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total[30m])\n            ) > 0.05\n          for: 5m\n          labels:\n            severity: critical\n          annotations:\n            summary: Multiarch image inspection failure rate is critically high.\n            message: >-\n              The multiarch-tuning-operator image inspection failure rate has exceeded\n              5% over the last 30 minutes. This indicates that a significant number of\n              pod image inspections are failing, which may prevent correct scheduling\n              gate removal and node affinity assignment for multi-architecture workloads.\n```\n\n### New file: `config/monitoring/kustomization.yaml`\n\n```yaml\nresources:\n- prometheus-rule.yaml\n```\n\n### Modified file: `config/prometheus/kustomization.yaml`\n\nAdd the monitoring resources alongside the existing ServiceMonitor:\n\n```yaml\nresources:\n- monitor.yaml\n- ../monitoring\n```\n\n---\n\n## What each piece does\n\n1. **`config/monitoring/prometheus-rule.yaml`** — The `PrometheusRule` CR. The `expr` divides the per-second rate of `mto_ppo_ctrl_failed_image_inspection_total` by the per-second rate of `mto_ppo_ctrl_processed_pods_total` over a 30-minute window. If that ratio exceeds 0.05 (5%) for 5 continuous minutes (`for: 5m`), the alert fires with `severity: critical`.\n\n2. **`config/monitoring/kustomization.yaml`** — Standard kustomize resource list for the new directory.\n\n3. **`config/prometheus/kustomization.yaml`** — Updated to include `../monitoring` so the PrometheusRule is deployed alongside the existing ServiceMonitor when the prometheus kustomize overlay is enabled.\n\n## Commands\n\nNo special make targets are needed. The file is deployed via kustomize when the prometheus overlay is enabled in `config/default/kustomization.yaml` (uncomment the `- ../prometheus` line). To verify the YAML is valid kustomize output:\n\n```bash\ncd config/prometheus && kustomize build .\n```"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":185,"cache_read_input_tokens":39156,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":185,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ee025f52-3815-4a77-bdcf-c262ea28ac5c","uuid":"ec1830d5-4e47-4174-a801-8c7119929ade","timestamp":"2026-07-20T14:16:08.398Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011CdDT5yY6AhQqZoCvDpLs3"}
